{
  "stem": "5559.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, as I said, I was about one year in Vienna's elementary.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then when I came to Czernowitz, because they were all very, big highly educated universities and everything.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were the-- what I started out and continued with my elementary-- thanks, God, I was quick-- quick to learn foreign language.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that what also I think I survived from all the ordeals what we had later on in my life.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Now right away I had to learn besides my language was naturally, it was German, Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then I had to learn Romanian, because that became Romania.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Then, all of a sudden, they switch.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was also part of Russia.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And in school was compulsory-- when I talk school, I'm talking higher education, not for elementary-- was compulsory to take French and English.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "In other words, it wasn't like I hear here, my kids here they can choose to have a foreign language or not have a foreign language.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Over there, French and English.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "If you want to pass the grades, that's what you learn.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I remember I had a teacher, private teacher, my father believed-- because he was [INAUDIBLE] also, you should learn foreign language, for English.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he always came and he used to say to me, I'll tell you, Mark.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I'm going teach you English like a taxi driver in New York.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because just plain he said, they're not much grammar, they're not much-- you know, but they speak English.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that's what I want you to learn, right there, English.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I never thought I wind up one day in English language.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "How did your parents get along with the non-Jewish community?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I would say they got along great, because they were involved that way.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
